adjective.description: (of an official or feudal lord) having local authority that elsewhere belongs only to a sovereign.

noun.description: Each of two bones within the skull forming parts of the eye socket, the nasal cavity, and the hard palate.

proper noun.description: A village in northeastern Illinois, northwest of Chicago; population 67,080 (est. 2008).

origin: Mid 17th century: from French palatin(e), from Latin palatum palate.
